claim.claim-text:
1. A die-cast seat cushion frame for vehicle seat, comprising: 
a forward frame portion defined forwardly thereof; 
a rearward frame portion defined rearwardly thereof; 
a pair of lateral frame portions defined between said forward and rearward frame portions; 
at least two connecting portions integrally formed in each of said pair of lateral frame portions, said at least two connecting portions being adapted for connection with a slide rail means; and 
a cross beam portion extended integrally between said pair of lateral frame sections in such a manner that one end of said cross beam portion is disposed at a point corresponding to one of said at least two connecting portions while another end of said cross beam section is disposed at a point corresponding to another of said at least two connecting portions.

12. A die-cast seat cushion frame for vehicle seat, comprising: 
a forward frame portion defined forwardly thereof; 
a rearward frame portion defined rearwardly thereof; 
a pair of lateral frame portions defined between said forward and rearward frame portions, wherein each of said pair of lateral frame portions has an integral upper flange projecting therefrom in a direction outwardly of the seat cushion frame and an integral lower flange projecting therefrom in a direction inwardly of the seat cushion frame; 
a reinforcing beam portion of generally U-shaped cross section defined between each of said pair of lateral frame portions and said integral lower flange; 
at least two connecting portions formed integrally dependent from each of said pair of lateral frame sections and said reinforcing beam portion, wherein said at least two connecting portions each has a thickness generally equal to a width of said reinforcing beam portion and are adapted for connection with a slide rail means; and 
a cross beam portion extended integrally between said pair of lateral frame portions in such a manner that one end of said cross beam portion is disposed at a point corresponding to one of said at least two connecting portions while another end of said cross beam portion is disposed at a point corresponding to another of said at least two connecting potions.

18. A die-cast seat cushion frame for vehicle seat, comprising: 
a forward frame portion defined forwardly thereof, said forward frame portion having an integral upper flange projecting therefrom in a direction outwardly of the seat cushion frame and an integral lower flange projecting therefrom in a direction inwardly of the seat cushion frame; 
a rearward frame portion defined rearwardly thereof; 
a pair of lateral frame portions defined between said forward and rearward frame portions, said pair of lateral frame portions each having an integral upper flange projecting therefrom in a direction outwardly of the seat cushion frame and an integral lower flange projecting therefrom in a direction inwardly of the seat cushion frame, wherein both said integral upper and lower flanges extend along a longitudinal direction of said pair of lateral frame portions, except that the lower flange portion has a discontinued area therein; 
said integral upper and lower flanges of said pair of lateral frame portions being connected integrally and continuously with said integral upper and lower flanges of said forward frame portion, respectively; 
a reinforcing beam portion of generally U-shaped cross section defined between each of said pair of lateral frame portions and said integral lower flange; 
at least two connecting portions formed integrally dependent from each of said pair of lateral frame portions and said reinforcing beam portion, said at least two connecting portions being adapted for connection with a slide rail means; and 
a cross beam portion extended integrally between said pair of lateral frame sections in such a manner that one end of said cross beam portion is disposed at a point corresponding to one of said at least two connecting portions while another end of said cross beam portion is disposed at a point corresponding to another of said at least two connecting potions, wherein said cross beam portion is of a generally inverted-U-shaped configuration in cross-section, comprising an upper horizontal wall, a pair of lateral vertical walls and a pair of flanges projecting outwardly and continuously from respective two ends of said pair of lateral vertical walls, and wherein said pair of flanges each terminates in integral and continuous connection with said lower flange of each of said pair of lateral frame portions at said discontinued area.
